# {{mul-kangxi radical-def}}

====Usage notes====
Do not confuse {{lang|mul|月}} with {{m|mul|⺼}}, a form of {{m|mul|肉||flesh, meat}} when used as the left-hand radical of a character. {{m|mul|⺼}} is used for parts of the body such as {{m|mul|背||back}} or {{m|mul|肝||liver}}. These may be written identically as {{lang|mul|月}}, but in careful use they are distinguished, with the inside of {{lang|mul|⺼}} being written with unattached diagonal strokes. This is particularly an issue in looking up characters by radical; compare the [[Appendix:Chinese radical/月|月 index]] and [[Appendix:Chinese radical/肉|肉 index]].

Older/orthodox forms such as the Kangxi dictionary forms may additionally distinguish components that are related to neither {{m|mul|月}} nor {{m|mul|肉}}, such as e.g. {{m|mul|朋}}, {{m|mul|前}} or {{m|mul|服}} where the two horizontal strokes {{m|mul|一}} would be written as two unattached dots {{m|mul|丶}} instead. Also, the bottom part of {{m|mul|青}}({{m|mul|靑}}) components would be written as {{m|mul|円}}. The orthodox {{lang|mul|月}} and {{m|mul|⺼}} components, while similar, would still be distinguished slightly: they both use horizontal strokes, but {{m|mul|⺼}} connects them to the {{m|mul|⺆}} shape on both sides, and {{lang|mul|月}} only connects them on the left side.

